    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I think it's not possible to decompress a archive file which is bigger than 1024 bytes, with the bz2 adapter.</p>

<p>In file Filter/Compress/Bz2.php :
164 
165       $compressed = bzread($file);
166       bzclose($file);</p>

<p>bzread PHP Doc says : 
string bzread ( resource $bz [, int $length = 1024 ] )</p>

<p>length</p>

<pre><code>If not specified, bzread() will read 1024 (uncompressed) bytes at a time. A maximum of 8192 uncompressed bytes will be read at a time.
</code></pre>

<p>I think that we need a sort of :
$compressed = '';
while (!feof($file)) {
  $compressed .= bzread($file);
}</p>

